<TITLE> PM promises fair wages for workers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 12 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has promised the implementation of fair wages for the workers. She made the assurance at a meeting with Sramik League leaders at her residence on Monday marking the 40th founding anniversary of the ruling Awami League's workers' organisation. Hasina said the government was well aware of the workers' problems and was trying to solve them in phases. The government has also decided to reopen all closed mills and factories in phases, she added. Sramik League general secretary Roy Ramesh said they had earlier placed floral wreaths at the portrait of 'Bangabandhu' Sheikh Mujibur Rahman at Dhanmondi 32 marking the day. The Sramik League workers went to the prime minister's residence at around 9:30am. The Labour Act would be made effective in line with the ILO convention, Roy Ramesh said, quoting the prime minister. bdne
